2026-06-17 | Maximum Product Cutting

	Question
Return the maximum product obtainable after at least one cut.
	Approach
Let:
		dp[i]
represent the maximum product obtainable from a rope of length i.
For every possible first cut j:
		j | (i-j)
Two possibilities exist for the second part:
		1. Don't cut further
				(i-j)
		2. Cut further
				dp[i-j]
Similarly for j.
So:
		dp[i] =
		max(
			j*(i-j),
			j*dp[i-j]
		)
for all j from 1 to i-1.
	Example
	n = 4
	Cuts:
		1 × 3 = 3
		2 × 2 = 4
	Maximum = 4
	Time Complexity
	O(n²)
	Space Complexity
	O(n)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    int maxProd(int n) {
        vector<int> dp(n + 1, 0);
        dp[1] = 1;
        for(int i = 2; i <= n; i++) {
            for(int j = 1; j < i; j++) {
                dp[i] = max(dp[i],
                            max(j * (i - j),
                                j * dp[i - j]));
            }
        }
        return dp[n];
    }
};
	Mathematical Optimization
There is a famous observation:
•	The product is maximized when the rope is cut into pieces of length 3 as much as possible.
Rules:
		n = 2 → 1
		n = 3 → 2
		if n % 3 == 0
				answer = 3^(n/3)
		if n % 3 == 1
				answer = 4 × 3^((n-4)/3)
		if n % 3 == 2
				answer = 2 × 3^(n/3)
	This gives:
	Time Complexity
	O(log n)
	Mathematical Solution
class Solution {
public:
    long long power(long long a, long long b) {
        long long res = 1;
        while(b) {
            if(b & 1)
                res *= a;
            a *= a;
            b >>= 1;
        }
        return res;
    }
    long long maxProd(int n) {
        if(n == 2) return 1;
        if(n == 3) return 2;
        if(n % 3 == 0)
            return power(3, n / 3);
        if(n % 3 == 1)
            return 4 * power(3, (n - 4) / 3);
        return 2 * power(3, n / 3);
    }
};
	Key Insight
Breaking a rope into pieces of length 3 produces the maximum product. The only exception is when a remainder 1 is left, where replacing:
		3 + 1
with
		2 + 2
increases the product from:
		3 × 1 = 3
to
		2 × 2 = 4
which leads to the optimal mathematical solution.
